cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NA

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - Spectral unmixing is a common technique used in remote sensing and image processing, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - Nonnegative matrix factorization (NMF) and its developments, which are widely used in spectral unmixing, are machine learning techniques. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The use of Lq norm and sparsity constraints in the proposed algorithm is related to information theory and signal processing. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The proposed algorithm is based on a network of single-node clusters, which can be considered as a social and information network. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The optimization strategy used in the proposed algorithm (diffusion least mean p-power) is a numerical analysis technique.
